                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-09-09</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This book is a good starting point for people to understand the work of embedded linux engineers in the real world. It is also a great book for experienced people in the industry as they can collect various pieces of missing information. I just wish I had this book two years back when I learnt all this stuff the hardway through pieces of information on web. Technology changes fast, but the stuff mentioned in the book is still up to date in the industry.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Useful reference for building or using embedded Linux</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
